<br>
<br>
Level 1-10: Get over to the newbie log and start whacking and whatnot. I hit level 4 in around an hour. Now go buy your Fire pet, run back to the newbie log and summon one until it cons yellow. Now start pulling mutiples and using your area affect. I was killing around 5 fire beetles at a time pretty easily. Next roam out into the woods a little and start killing bears and skeletons and move over to the undead ruins and start killing skeletons and stuff, you'll be level 8 in no time. Again, get that fire pet, summon a yellow and stay at the ruins until level 10.<br>
<br>
<br>
Level 11-12: Move out into East Commons and start killing anything blue or even. This includes asp, Kodiaks, basically anything that gives you XP. Side note: If you get poisoned from a snake and you know you are going to die GATE. There is some kinda bug that is actually usefull, when you return to your bind point you will be at half health and all your buffs gone(bad) BUT the poison will be gone also(good). Doesn't take long at all to hit level 12.<br>
<br>
<br>
Level 12-20: Get yet another fire pet and go to The Overthere. Bind yourself either at the vedors or at the bank. Now face Warsliks Woods and start running towards it, you will see a bunch of mobs that will be red to you and con &quot;scowls ready to attack&quot;. They will not however attack you(excluding Sarnaks). Move to the canyon edge that harbors the Skorpikis(sic) and start hugging it untill you are on the WW side of it. Now look around and you should see things like &quot;a sabertooth cat&quot;, &quot;a sarnak youth&quot;, and some kind of succulants. Most of these will con even or blue to you, with some yellows. Get that fire pet up and have him guard near the canyon edge and start pulling. Try to avoid pulling Sarnak Flunkies because they are pretty tough until you get your 16 pets. You can sit in this one spot until level 16. Now go get your new spells and gate back to the outpost. This time just move out towards the WW side of the outpost and kill anything you see(sarnak conscripts are a little harder but still doable) Don't be afraid to melee some, while you are medding you will heal fast with phantom armor up. Stay here until level 20.<br>
<br>
<br>
Level 20-24: Make sure you have all your new spells and go to South Karana. Find the hermits hut and make a hotkey &quot;/say Kill you&quot;. Move to the chimney, stick you nose in and click it. The Hermit will attack you and your level 20 fire pet will eat him pretty fast with help from you. His spawn time is 2 minutes and he is absolutely awsome xp. I stayed here until 24. Be careful not to go afk because every now and then a Tesch Mas Gnoll will wander past and aggro on you, if that happens sick pet on it and gate back to the bridge and camp to clear aggro.<br>
<br>
<br>
Level 24-29: Treants. These guys are really nice xp and give nice loot to boot. I rarely had a problem joining a treant group but sometimes had a problem forming one due to the bad faction you get with Qeynos and Druids. On occasion when I couldn't form one I would go pay a visit to the Hermit again. You can get nice xp here past level 29 actaully but once you ding I have a better place to hunt.<br>
<br>
<br>
level 29-37: Gather your new spells and your fire pet, bind at the pillar in Oasis(to the side of the dock in the water) and make sure you bring lots of cat's eye agate and malachites. (Don't bind at the docks because more often than not when you gate/die there will be specs or SG's waiting to smash you due to people training there) Now get on the raft and go to Timorous Deep. Summon one or 2 waterstones and start the very very long swim to location -9000, -6000(roughly). If you could get Dead man floating from a necromancer you can run there much faster than swimming, Levitate usually fades before you reach the island but DMF last over an hour. You will see a big iceberg, and thats what you want to climb up onto. Make sure to invis yourself when you get near it because the mobs there will aggro on you. Now find the side of the glacier with &quot;golra's&quot; (not Hulking Golra's) You should see a wrecked ship on the iceberg, set up camp near it, but not too near it because there is a golra inside that will aggro on you. Now summon a good fire pet, hand it two Swords of Runes and pull a golra with malise. There are at least 7 golra spawns on that side and they can all be easily single pulled. These guys are awsome xp and really easy. When you hit 34 gate and go buy your new spells and make sure you have that 34 fire pet again, come back and stay until 37. Some of them will start turning green at 36 but they are still xp green and with 7 spawns it doesn't matter.<br>
<br>
<br>
Level 37-39: I hated these two levels. I ended up going to The Overthere and grouping till 39. You can solo here, and it may actually be faster to solo, just don't try the sarnak knights or Sabertooth Tigers becuase they are mean as hell.<br>
<br>
<br>
level 39-44: Go to Dreadlands. As you zone in from FM, turn right as you come out of the cave and start running till you hit the corner. You should see a cave mouth there(snow cave). Now I bet your sick of looking at this type of mob but they, like their brethren are awsome xp. &quot;a Tundra Yeti&quot; is what you are after and in this cave are at least 7 spawns, and sometimes one or two roaming spawns. The roaming spawns are mostly Tundra yetis but can also be Drolvargs, ****atrices and Drachnids. If a drolvarg spawns gate back to the entrance to Dreadlands and take a break, the non Tundra Yeti spawns will eventually roam out of the cave and not come back. I used fire pet here too and you have to start making an effort now to outdamage your pet. These guys are actually spawned close together but they are blind as a bat, easily single pulled with malise. Stay here till 44.<br>
<br>
<br>
Level 44-49: These levels really sucked. I ended up back at the Tundra Yeti cave till I hit 45, then tried several other places(45 REALLY sucks) I ended up back in The Overthere with my 44 Fire pet soloing anything blue(mostly Sarnak Knights and Sabertooth Tigers with occasional cacti and chickens) As soon as you get 46 head back to Dreadlands. Grouping here, in my experience really blows for xp. Try to grab a mage partner, or even a wizard if you can and head out towards the Giant Fortress in the snow. No you aren't going to kill giants. Now behind the fortress and over the hill you will see what looks to be an abandoned stone house that is falling apart. If you walk up to it and have a look inside you will see a cave. Head on in and get your fire pet up again and start killing &quot;a glacier yeti&quot;. There are 2 roaming ones and 4 static spawns in the end room of the cave. If you have a mage partner have one use an earth pet and the other a fire or air pet. These guys can be single pulled also, even though they are standing on top of one another. Once I hit level 48 I was able to pretty much hold the whole cave by myself using a fire pet. You'll be 49 in no time here compared to grouping.<br>
<br>
<br>
Level 49-???: Go ahead and make a point to get all of your 49 pets, you will be using them for quite some time. I went back to the Glacier Yeti cave from 49-50 and it only took about 4 hours with my new bad to the bone fire pet. Upon level 50 I targeted a glacier yeti and did a big /rude and vowed to never, ever, ever again look upon another snow monkey. At 50 I went to Ocean of Tears and set up camp on the shoreline of Seafury Island. Get up your 49 fire pet, Cast Burnout 3 and med until he Damage Shields himself. Now go pull one of the many seafury cyclops back to your pet(you don't even need JBoots because they are slow.) Now have a seat, keep the seafury targeted and start hitting your /pet health report hotkey. Amazingly almost every 49 fire pet can solo a seafury. Now when the cyclops starts to run away start casting your 44 shock and type /pet get lost. Right before the spell cast hit enter, causing your pet to suicide. This way you get full xp for the kill and you dont have to waste time waiting for &quot;Goner&quot; to heal up. Summon a new fire pet, BO3 him and med until he DS's himself and repeat. I went from 50-51 in about 6 hours here and made some nice loot to boot. There is pretty much no downtime involved in this since you are medding during the entire fight, only occasionally Lava Bolting to even out your pets odds of winning. You can also just reclaim your pet when the cyclops starts to run but I was too lazy. Watch out for Quag Maelstrom, he is a named seafury and is a bard, you can easily recognize him, he always has a huge horn in his hand. I saw him kill a level 55 bard that was trying to kite him around, but I got tired of looking at him and decided to chain cast him to death. Took me 5 level 49 earth pets casting BO3 and Lava Shield but I did it, he drops a no drop horn that is all/all and is used for the bard epic everytime. Don't bother with him, not worth the mana.<br>
<br>
<br>
Good luck fellow mages, hope you level as fast as I have. If you have any questions and are on Tunare server please feel free to message me, providing I'm not in the midst of battle I would be glad to assist in any way I can. Currently working on my epic, taking a break from leveling for awhile. /bye<br>
