en nuke once again.  If I was FM when i pulled i would stand there beating the hell outta them with my torch, stepping back to get a nuke in every now and then.  Just make sure you wipe one out, then while your pet is healing you should be medding/healing until pet is 100% health again then move to the next one.  Like I said, at 29 you can only kill about 4-5 of them before you have to take a good med break.  Bythe time you hit 34 you are waiting on them most of the time evnen after killing all 7 spawns.  Hope this helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=balthemal>Balthemal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#333333>(5/28/01 10:04:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Level 1-51 fast and easy (Dark Elf)</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the info. I'm pretty sure I figured out what I was doing wrong. I had no focus items <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  SO, I bit the bullet and bought those expensive gems (140pp for a ruby, ouch).<br>
