ing wrong but I suspect your a) Nuking too soon(I would let pet taunt once or twice, nuke, sit, wait and nuke again) b) You either don't have the focus item for your fire pet or you aren't holding it when summoning your pet.  As for Golras resisting malise. yes they have moderate resist for their level but its been a while since I was there, they could have upped their resist.  You should at lvl 32 only be spendinfg about 15-20% max per golra.  I had 200 int + mana stuff at that level so your percentage of mana used should be a little higher if you are not what I was at then. (This is Sarfa by the way, this is my mage, Sarfa is my Necromancer.)  And for the previous poster, fire pets DS is not considered damage done my the pet, or anyone for that matter, same as any DS cast on anyone/thing, it counts as environmental damage I believe(such as falling).  By the way, this guide may not be as effective now that Fire Pet's DS's have been nerfed.  Luckily I was able to get through all those level before then. (If you haven't heard, pets that cast DS's including the epic pet sometimes take up to and beyond 20 minutes now, nowhere near as fast as 30 seconds max back when I was fighting with Fire pets)  And for Murlow, yes there was a romaing mob or maybe two if I'm not mistaked at the 1st eti cave mentioned in DL, but thankfully they don't pop very often.  If im'm not mistaken their spawn time is 2.5 hours OR they spawn just as fast and roam off and as long as they are not killed they wander until they are killed, causing them to pop again in the back of the cave.  As for a safe spot to pull in the cave, just pull to a room wall, as you know the yeti's cave &gt;tiny&lt; aggro ranges and if you pull there the only add you might get is the widow/drolvarg roamer(s), and only them because they have a loarger aggro radius. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uadabpyron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adab Pyron</A> at: 12/15/01 2:15:04 am<br></i></td></tr></tabl